 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 Revenue Chart (SVG bar chart, color-only series encoding)\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 Escalated perspectives confirmed\n\nRunning the full JTBD checklist for the perspectives escalated by a11y-critic:\n\n- **Magnification & Reflow** \u2014 MEDIUM\n- **Environmental Contrast** \u2014 HIGH\n- **Keyboard & Motor Access** \u2014 MEDIUM\n- **Screen Reader & Semantic Structure** \u2014 MEDIUM\n\n**At LOW (not reviewed):** Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Auditory Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent.\n\nLine references below point at the fixture code in the audit request.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 1 \u2014 Magnification & Reflow (MEDIUM)\n\n**WCAG (AA):** 1.4.4, 1.4.10, 1.4.12, 1.4.13, 2.4.11\n\n| # | JTBD item | Result | Note |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1.4.10 | Reflows to single column at 320px, no horizontal scroll | **FINDING (MINOR)** | `<svg>` is fixed 600\u00d7360 with no `viewBox` and no `max-width` rule \u2192 cannot shrink. 1.4.10 exempts 2D-layout content (charts qualify), so not a strict AA failure, but the chart forces horizontal scroll and cannot zoom-to-fit. |\n| 2.4.11 | Focused elements never obscured by sticky UI | N/A | No sticky/fixed elements; no focusable elements in the component. |\n| 1.4.4 | Text scales to 200% without loss | PASS (with note) | SVG scales under full-page zoom, so 1.4.4 is met. The 10px y-axis base (line 52) is small and compounds low-vision friction, but page zoom addresses the criterion. |\n| 1.4.12 | Adapts to text-spacing overrides | PASS / N/A | HTML legend (`.legend-label`) reflows under spacing overrides. SVG `<text>` is positioned by x/y attributes \u2014 overrides neither reflow nor clip it (N/A for the SVG). |\n| 1.4.13 | Hover/focus content is dismissible, hoverable, persistent | **FINDING (CRITICAL)** | Tooltip is hover-only, rendered above the bar with no hover bridge, no Escape dismiss, and no way to move the pointer onto it. |\n\n**Red flags:** \"Tooltip disappears before magnifier user can reach it\" \u2014 **FIRES** (auto-CRITICAL).\n\n**Finding:** The value tooltip is triggered only by `onMouseEnter`/`onMouseLeave` on the bar and is drawn above the bar (`tooltip.y - 22`) with no hover bridge, no Escape-to-dismiss, and no pointer handlers of its own. A screen-magnifier or pointer-zoom user who moves toward the tooltip to read it leaves the bar's hit area, `onMouseLeave` fires, and the tooltip vanishes before it can be read. The tooltip is the only source of exact values, so those figures are entirely unreachable for this user group (approximate values remain perceivable from bar heights against the labeled y-axis).\n**WCAG:** 1.4.13 Content on Hover or Focus (AA)\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** CRITICAL (red flag)\n**Route to:** UX Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `<rect ... onMouseEnter={() => setTooltip(...)} onMouseLeave={() => setTooltip(null)} />` (lines 70\u201378); tooltip `<g>` with no pointer handlers (lines 92\u201399); no `keydown`/Escape handler anywhere in the component.\n**Fix:** Make the revealed content hoverable (keep it open while the pointer is over the bar *or* the tooltip), dismissible via Escape without moving the pointer, and persistent until dismissed. The robust fix is to stop relying on a transient hover target for essential data \u2014 surface exact values in an accessible data table (see the 1.1.1 fix) so magnifier users are not dependent on a vanishing tooltip.\n\n**Finding:** The `<svg>` has fixed pixel `width`/`height` (600\u00d7360) and no `viewBox`, and there is no `.revenue-chart { max-width: 100% }` rule, so it cannot scale down. At a 320px-equivalent viewport (400% zoom) the chart forces horizontal scrolling and cannot shrink to fit.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.10 Reflow (AA) \u2014 2D-layout exception applies\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `<svg width={CHART_W} height={CHART_H + 60} className=\"revenue-chart\">` (lines 40\u201344); `CHART_W = 600` (line 27); no `viewBox`; no `.revenue-chart` CSS rule.\n**Fix:** Add `viewBox=\"0 0 600 360\"` and set `width=\"100%\"` / `max-width` with `height=\"auto\"` so the chart scales into narrow and zoomed viewports; keep the data table (1.1.1 fix) as the reliable path to exact values at any zoom.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 2 \u2014 Environmental Contrast (HIGH)\n\n**WCAG (AA):** 1.3.3, 1.4.1, 1.4.3, 1.4.11\n\n| # | JTBD item | Result | Note |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1.4.3 | Normal text \u2265 4.5:1 | **PASS** | Y-axis `#666` on white = 5.74:1 (small text, meets 4.5:1); x-axis `#333` = 12.6:1; tooltip `#fff` on `#333` = 12.6:1; h2/legend near-black on white. |\n| 1.4.3 | Large text \u2265 3:1 | PASS / N/A | No large text below threshold. |\n| 1.4.11 | Graphical-object & UI-boundary contrast \u2265 3:1 | **PASS** | Every bar fill vs the white plot background \u2265 4.6:1 (`#e65100` lowest at 4.6:1) \u2014 all clear 3:1. Bars are separated by 12px white gaps, so no bar-to-bar adjacency requirement. Legend swatches \u2265 4.6:1 vs white. |\n| 1.4.1 | Color never the sole indicator | **FINDING (MINOR)** | Color is redundant here \u2014 bars carry x-axis text labels and legend rows pair each swatch with a text name \u2014 but it is fragile (see finding). |\n| 1.3.3 | No sensory-only instructions | PASS / N/A | No \"click the red\u2026\" style instructions. |\n| \u2014 | Functional in forced-colors mode | **FINDING (MINOR \u2014 folded into 1.4.1)** | Legend swatches use inline `background-color`, remapped to a single system color in forced-colors \u2192 legend color key collapses (text names preserve the mapping). |\n\n**Red flags:** Body text below 3:1 \u2014 not firing (lowest text 5.74:1). Error state color-only \u2014 no error states present. Interactive element indistinguishable in forced-colors \u2014 bars are not keyboard controls and remain identified by x-axis labels; not fired as auto-CRITICAL.\n\n**Finding:** Series are encoded by fill color, and the legend maps color\u2192region with color-only swatches (no shape, pattern, or icon). This is **mitigated** in the current markup: every bar carries its region name as an x-axis text label and every legend row pairs its swatch with a text name, so color is redundant rather than the sole means of conveying information. Residual risk keeps it a live finding: if x-axis labels truncate (11px text in an ~88px slot) or the chart evolves to grouped/stacked series, color becomes load-bearing and fails for color-blind users; and in forced-colors mode the swatch `background-color` is remapped to one system color, collapsing the legend's color key.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.1 Use of Color (A)\n**Perspective:** Environmental Contrast\n**Severity:** MINOR (color is redundant with text labels; workaround always available)\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `fill={region.fill}` as sole bar differentiator (line 75); `.legend-swatch` is color-only (CSS lines 148\u2013153); swatch `style={{ backgroundColor: r.fill }}` (line 106). Mitigation present: x-axis `<text>{region.name}</text>` (lines 79\u201387) and legend `<span className=\"legend-label\">{r.name}</span>` (line 107).\n**Fix:** Add a non-color channel for defense-in-depth \u2014 SVG `<pattern>`/texture fills or distinct shape markers per series, mirrored in the legend swatches \u2014 and prefer direct value labels on/above bars. Give swatches a visible `border` (or `forced-color-adjust` handling) so the legend key survives forced-colors. Guarantee x-axis labels never truncate.\n\n**Calibration note (friction):** The HIGH alarm on Environmental Contrast is **not borne out by the evidence.** Every measured contrast ratio passes AA (the fixture's own CSS comment confirms the fills at 4.6\u20137.2:1), and the \"color-only encoding\" is redundant with text labels on both the bars and the legend. The genuine barriers in this component are *not* contrast \u2014 they are the missing text alternative (screen reader) and the mouse-only value reveal (keyboard/magnification). Rating the color encoding CRITICAL because the fixture comment says \"WCAG 1.4.1\" would be dead output: it would ignore that the x-axis labels already provide the non-color path the criterion requires. Residual severity is MINOR.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 5 \u2014 Keyboard & Motor Access (MEDIUM)\n\n**WCAG (AA):** 1.3.4, 2.1.1, 2.1.2, 2.4.1, 2.4.3, 2.4.7, 2.4.13, 2.5.1, 2.5.2, 2.5.3, 2.5.7, 2.5.8\n\n| # | JTBD item | Result | Note |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 2.1.1 | All interactive elements keyboard-operable | **FINDING (MAJOR)** | Bars reveal values only on mouse hover; no `onFocus`/`tabIndex`/key handler. Exact values unreachable by keyboard. |\n| 2.1.2 | No keyboard traps | PASS | No focusable custom widgets; nothing to trap. |\n| 2.4.1 | Skip link to main | N/A | Page-level; out of scope for a single component. |\n| 2.4.3 | Logical focus order | N/A | No focusable elements. |\n| 2.4.7 / 2.4.13 | Visible focus indicator | N/A (now) | No focusable elements today; becomes required by the keyboard fix. |\n| 2.5.1 | Multi-point gestures have single-pointer alt | PASS / N/A | No multi-point gestures. |\n| 2.5.2 | Activation on up-event | PASS / N/A | Reveal is hover, not down-event activation. |\n| 2.5.3 | Visible label matches accessible name | N/A | No labeled controls. |\n| 2.5.7 | Drag has click alternative | PASS / N/A | No drag interactions. |\n| 2.5.8 | Targets \u2265 24\u00d724 CSS px | PASS | Bars are 88px wide; shortest (Africa & ME) \u2248 56px tall \u2014 all hover targets exceed 24\u00d724. Legend items are non-interactive. |\n| 1.3.4 | Portrait + landscape | PASS / N/A | No orientation lock. |\n\n**Red flags:** \"Interactive element unreachable by keyboard\" \u2014 the mouse-only value reveal is unreachable by keyboard. Calibrated below.\n\n**Finding:** Each bar exposes its exact value only through the mouse-hover tooltip; there is no `onFocus`/`onBlur`, no `tabIndex`, and no keyboard path to reveal a value. A sighted keyboard-only user can estimate values from bar heights against the y-axis gridline labels but cannot obtain the exact figures.\n**WCAG:** 2.1.1 Keyboard (A)\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `<rect ... onMouseEnter=... onMouseLeave=... />` (lines 70\u201378) \u2014 mouse handlers only; no `onFocus`, `tabIndex`, or key handler on the bars or the `<svg>`.\n**Fix:** Provide keyboard access to the same data. Preferred: the accessible data table from the 1.1.1 fix makes every value keyboard- and AT-reachable without adding roving focus to SVG bars. If interactive bars are wanted, make each bar focusable (`tabindex=\"0\"` + an appropriate role with an accessible name that already contains the value), mirror the hover reveal on `onFocus`/`onBlur`, add a visible \u22652px / \u22653:1 focus indicator (2.4.7/2.4.13), and support Escape (1.4.13).\n**Calibration:** The red flag would push auto-CRITICAL, but I rate this **MAJOR** \u2014 the chart's primary message (relative revenue by region) is carried by visible bar heights against a labeled axis, so keyboard users are not fully blocked; only the exact figures are keyboard-inaccessible.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 6 \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n\n**WCAG (AA):** 1.1.1, 1.3.1, 1.3.2, 2.4.2, 2.4.4, 2.4.6, 3.1.1, 3.1.2, 3.3.1, 3.3.2, 4.1.2, 4.1.3\n\n| # | JTBD item | Result | Note |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1.1.1 | Informative image has text alternative | **FINDING (CRITICAL)** | `<svg>` has no `role=\"img\"`, no accessible name, no `<title>`/`<desc>`, no data-table/offscreen equivalent. |\n| 4.1.2 | Custom widget has correct role | **FINDING (folded into CRITICAL)** | The data-viz `<svg>` exposes no role \u2014 a graphic with no name/role. |\n| 4.1.3 | Status messages use `aria-live` | **FINDING (folded into CRITICAL)** | Tooltip value is not in a live region \u2014 and is mouse-only, so AT never receives it regardless. |\n| 1.3.1 | Landmark regions | N/A (page scope) | `<section>` is unnamed \u2192 not exposed as a region landmark; the `<h2>` provides navigable structure, which is acceptable at component scope. |\n| 2.4.6 | Logical, descriptive headings | PASS | `<h2>Q1 2026 Revenue by Region</h2>` (line 37) is descriptive; h1 is page-level. |\n| 1.3.2 | DOM order matches reading order | PASS | Source order (axis \u2192 bars/labels \u2192 tooltip) is logical. |\n| 2.4.2 / 3.1.1 / 3.1.2 | Title / lang / foreign-language | N/A | Page-level; out of component scope. |\n| 2.4.4 | Link text | N/A | No links. |\n| 3.3.1 / 3.3.2 | Form labels / error association | N/A | No form inputs or errors. |\n\n**Red flags:** \"Custom widget with no ARIA role\" \u2014 **FIRES** (the data-viz `<svg>` has no role/name). Supports CRITICAL. No `<main>` / missing `lang` / unlabeled inputs are page-level or absent.\n\n**Finding:** The SVG data visualization has no `role=\"img\"`, no accessible name (`aria-label`/`aria-labelledby`), no in-SVG `<title>`/`<desc>`, and no text equivalent (data table or visually-hidden summary). Screen reader users receive no usable information from the chart; worse, the exact revenue values exist **only** inside a mouse-hover tooltip that assistive-technology users never trigger, so even the underlying data has no programmatic representation anywhere in the DOM.\n**WCAG:** 1.1.1 Non-text Content (A); compounded by 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value and 4.1.3 Status Messages\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** CRITICAL\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** `<svg width={CHART_W} height={CHART_H + 60} className=\"revenue-chart\">` (lines 40\u201344) \u2014 no role or ARIA name. Values only assigned inside the hover handler: `onMouseEnter={() => setTooltip({ ... text: \\`${region.name}: $${region.value}M\\` })}` (lines 76\u201377). No `<table>` or offscreen text equivalent anywhere in the component.\n**Fix:** Add `role=\"img\"` plus a concise `aria-label` (or `aria-labelledby`/`aria-describedby` referencing `<title>`+`<desc>`), **and** provide a real text equivalent for the data \u2014 a visually-associated `<table>` of region/value pairs (best; also fixes keyboard, magnification, and cognitive access to exact figures) or, at minimum, a visually-hidden list. The chart summary should state the metric, period, and the ranked figures.\n\n---\n\n## Contract-compatible blocks (new CRITICAL/MAJOR findings)\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: dataviz_svg_no_text_alternative\nfingerprint: 7f3a9c1e0b52\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.1.1 Non-text Content (+ 4.1.2, 4.1.3); WAI-ARIA APG img/graphics pattern\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 502.2 / WCAG 2.0 1.1.1 A \u2014 applies\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=HIGH (was MEDIUM), keyboard_motor=MEDIUM, magnification=MEDIUM\nevidence: fixture lines 40-44 (`<svg>` no role/name); lines 76-77 (values only in mouse hover handler); no data table/offscreen text\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 SR walkthrough would land on an unnamed graphic with no data equivalent\nexpected_behavior: SR announces chart name/purpose and can reach every region/value pair as text\nactual_behavior: SR receives an unnamed graphic; exact values exist only in a mouse-hover tooltip and are never exposed to AT\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: dataviz_tooltip_not_hoverable_dismissible\nfingerprint: b21d64f8ae90\nsource: perspective-audit Magnification & Reflow checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.4.13 Content on Hover or Focus\nsection_508_fpc_context: WCAG 2.0 has no 1.4.13 equivalent \u2014 WCAG 2.1/2.2 AA only; \"not in scope\" for the 2.0-based 508 baseline\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: magnification=HIGH (was MEDIUM), keyboard_motor=MEDIUM\nevidence: fixture lines 70-78 (hover-only rect), lines 92-99 (tooltip g, no pointer handlers); no Escape handler\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 magnifier user hovers bar, moves pointer toward tooltip, leaves bar hit area, tooltip unmounts\nexpected_behavior: revealed content is hoverable, Escape-dismissible, and persistent until dismissed\nactual_behavior: tooltip unmounts on mouseleave of the bar before it can be reached; sole source of exact values\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: dataviz_values_mouse_only\nfingerprint: c9e05a7742b1\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 2.1.1 Keyboard\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 / WCAG 2.0 2.1.1 A \u2014 applies\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=HIGH (was MEDIUM)\nevidence: fixture lines 70-78 \u2014 mouse handlers only; no onFocus/tabIndex/key handler on bars or svg\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 Tab reaches no bar; no keyboard path reveals a value\nexpected_behavior: keyboard users can reach each value (focusable bars or an accessible data table)\nactual_behavior: exact values reachable by mouse hover only; keyboard users limited to estimating from bar heights\ntrend: new\n\n---\n\n## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** Revenue Chart (SVG bar chart, color-only series encoding)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Keyboard & Motor Access, Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Auditory Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 2 |\n| MAJOR | 1 |\n| MINOR | 2 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 0 |\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\n- None fully passed. **Environmental Contrast (HIGH) cleared every CRITICAL/MAJOR-level check** \u2014 all contrast ratios pass AA and color is redundant with text labels \u2014 leaving only a MINOR robustness finding; the HIGH escalation was not supported by the evidence.\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- SVG has no text alternative / role / data equivalent \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.1.1 (+4.1.2, 4.1.3)\n- Bar values reachable by mouse hover only, no keyboard path \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.1.1\n\n**UX Design**\n- Tooltip not hoverable / not Escape-dismissible \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.4.13\n\n**Visual Design**\n- Color-only series encoding (redundant but fragile; forced-colors swatch collapse) \u2014 Environmental Contrast \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.1\n- SVG fixed size / no `viewBox` \u2014 cannot scale to narrow/zoomed viewports \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.10\n\n**Content Author**\n- (Secondary on the 1.1.1 CRITICAL) Author the chart's text summary and the region/value data-table content.\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n- **Chart summary/description quality** \u2014 once a `role=\"img\"` name and/or data table is authored, the accuracy and adequacy of that text cannot be confirmed from source. *[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]*\n- **X-axis label truncation** \u2014 verify \"North America\" / \"Latin America\" (11px in ~88px slots) and any future/localized data do not clip at target breakpoints, since color is redundant only while labels remain legible. *[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]*\n- **Palette under CVD simulation** \u2014 the text labels mitigate color reliance today; if labels are ever removed or the chart becomes multi-series, verify the five fills remain distinguishable under deuteranopia/protanopia simulation. *[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]*\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**BLOCK** \u2014 two CRITICAL findings (no screen-reader text alternative for the data; hover tooltip unreachable by magnifier/pointer-zoom users, and it is the only source of exact values). A single fix resolves most of the barrier surface: add `role=\"img\"` + accessible name to the SVG and expose the region/value data as an associated, keyboard-reachable table. That one change clears the 1.1.1 CRITICAL, gives keyboard users the exact values (2.1.1 MAJOR), and removes magnifier dependence on the vanishing tooltip (1.4.13 CRITICAL). The two MINOR findings (add non-color encoding for defense-in-depth; add `viewBox` for scaling) should follow but do not by themselves block shipping.\n",
